---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const updated = 'June 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Use — Estimates, Not Advice | NestMath"
  description="NestMath terms of use: free educational financial calculators provided as-is, without warranty. Estimates only, not financial, tax, or legal advice."
  canonical="https://nestmath.app/terms"
  schemaName="NestMath Terms of Use"
  schemaDescription="Terms of use for NestMath free financial calculators. Estimates for educational use only."
>
  <div class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div
      class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[500px] h-[500px] rounded-full bg-primary-accent/20 blur-[120px] pointer-events-none -translate-y-1/4 translate-x-1/4"
      aria-hidden="true"
    ></div>

    <div class="max-w-[768px] mx-auto px-[24px] py-[64px]">
      <div class="mb-[48px]">
        <h1 class="text-headline-xl font-bold text-on-surface leading-tight -tracking-[0.02em] mb-[12px]">
          Terms of Use
        </h1>
        <p class="text-label-sm text-on-surface-variant">Last updated {updated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-[40px]">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Not financial advice</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            NestMath provides calculators and educational content for general informational purposes only.
            Nothing on this site is financial, investment, tax, accounting, or legal advice, and nothing here
            creates an advisor relationship. Every result is an estimate based on the assumptions you enter and
            on general formulas and tax or rate values that change over time. Before making any financial
            decision, confirm the numbers and consult a qualified professional who can account for your full
            situation.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Accuracy and assumptions</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            We work to keep the math correct and the assumptions current, and the calculation logic is open
            source so anyone can review it. Even so, the tools may contain errors, use simplified models, or
            rely on figures that have since changed. Tax brackets, contribution limits, and similar values are
            labeled with the year they reflect where relevant. We make no guarantee that any result is accurate,
            complete, or applicable to your circumstances.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Provided "as is"</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            The site and all tools are provided "as is" and "as available," without warranties of any kind,
            express or implied, including any implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular
            purpose, or non-infringement. To the fullest extent permitted by law, ArcLayer LLC and the site's
            contributors are not liable for any loss or damages arising out of your use of, or reliance on, the
            site or its results.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, in no event will ArcLayer LLC, its members, or contributors
            be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or for any loss
            of profits, savings, data, or goodwill, arising out of or related to your use of, or inability to
            use, the site or its results — whether based in contract, tort, negligence, strict liability, or any
            other theory, and even if advised of the possibility of such damages. Because the site is provided
            free of charge, the total aggregate liability of ArcLayer LLC for all claims relating to the site
            will not exceed the greater of the amount you paid to use it (which is zero) or one hundred US
            dollars ($100). Some jurisdictions do not allow certain limitations, so parts of this section may
            not apply to you.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Indemnification</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            You agree to indemnify and hold harmless ArcLayer LLC, its members, and contributors from any
            claims, losses, liabilities, damages, costs, or expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising
            out of your use or misuse of the site, your reliance on its results, your violation of these terms,
            or your presentation of any result as professional advice to another person.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Governing law and venue</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Kansas, United States, without regard to its
            conflict-of-laws rules. Any dispute arising out of or relating to the site or these terms will be
            brought exclusively in the state or federal courts located in Kansas, and you consent to the
            personal jurisdiction of those courts. If any provision of these terms is found unenforceable, the
            remaining provisions stay in full effect.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Acceptable use</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            Use the site lawfully and don't attempt to disrupt it, abuse it, or misrepresent its results as
            professional advice to others. The NestMath source code is open source under the license stated in
            its
            <a href="https://github.com/paynekerz/NestMath" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline">GitHub repository</a>;
            your use of the code is governed by that license.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-headline-md font-semibold text-on-surface mb-[12px]">Changes and contact</h2>
          <p class="text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            We may update these terms as the site changes. Continued use after an update means you accept the
            revised terms. The site is operated by ArcLayer LLC. Questions can be raised through the GitHub
            repository.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
